(registered 2020-01-14, last updated 2020-01-14)

Header field name:
Isolation

Applicable protocol:
http (RFC 2616)

Status:
Provisional

Author/Change controller:
OASIS Open Data Protocol (OData) TC, https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/odata/

Comments on the specification may be sent to odata-comment&lists.oasis-open.org. The email list is open to all interested parties. Subscription is required following the instructions at https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/comments/index.php?wg_abbrev=odata. The list archive can be reached at https://lists.oasis-open.org/archives/odata-comment/

For general information on OASIS, please contact Chet Ensign, chet.ensign&oasis-open.org, OASIS Open (https://www.oasis-open.org)

Specification document(s):
OData Version 4.01 Part 1: Protocol -
http://docs.oasis-open.org/odata/odata/v4.01/odata-v4.01-part1-protocol.html#sec_HeaderIsolationODataIsolation

Related information:
This provisional registration request is related to the request for permanent registration of four OData request headers submitted on 23 August 2019 in https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/ietf-message-headers/jf0XDAqbz2PE3MPcV1dRl6ROE4U. This provisional request is made to support legacy implementations using the header field 'Isolation.' The OData TC strongly recommends implementers use the header field 'OData-Isolation' as described in the permanent registration request and the OData Version 4.01 specification.